race.comment: ALL TOO SINGLE (4) was safely held on debut then improved sharply second outing when found the line hard to place, beaten less than a length. Has upside and is expected to go close again. FORT OF DREAMS (1) was well fancied on debut over 1000m and found the line strongly. Can only be improved and expected to run into the finish again. SNITCHY (9) has two duck eggs so far but wasn't far away on debut and then tackled a far richer maiden latest. Wouldn't shock to see a far improved run at this level. NORDIC STRIKE (2) resumes from a length break after making debut on heavy ground over the winter when he didn't go a yard. Keep very safe second time around.
